TSA agreed to make changes after ACLU filed official complaint . 
 Training will begin at Los Angeles International Airport . 
 TSA also told ACLU the new training will stress 'race neutrality' and will  emphasize 'hair pat-downs of African-American female travelers'Agency said they will also track down pat-down complaints filed by African-American women to assess if discrimination is occurring at specific airports . 
 In 2012 Solange Knowles claimed she had been racially targeted for a pat-down because she wore her hair in the Afro style . 
 